{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/learning-php/part5/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Konnor's Blog","author":"Konnor Rogers"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c057f5e2-79df-53d1-82b6-23ee11567da6","excerpt":"Part 5 Laracasts main site\nLaracasts - PHP for beginners Chapters covered: Chapter 10 - Functions Chapter 10 - Functions Functions are simple, but very powerful…","html":"<h1>Part 5</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://laracasts.com\">Laracasts main site</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners\">Laracasts - PHP for beginners</a></p>\n<h2>Chapters covered:</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners/episodes/10\">Chapter 10 - Functions</a></p>\n<h3>Chapter 10 - Functions</h3>\n<p>Functions are simple, but very powerful reusable pieces of code. They are the\nbuilding blocks of any language. Lets see how they help shape PHP.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"96703839850231450000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.php\n<?php\n\n// Will echo the values of \\$one, \\$two, and \\$three onto your web page\nfunction dumper(\\$one, \\$two, \\$three){\n  var_dump(\\$one, \\$two, \\$three);\n}`, `96703839850231450000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Will echo the values of $one, $two, and $three onto your web page</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">dumper</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$one</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$two</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$three</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">var_dump</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$one</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$two</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$three</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Lets break it down.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">function</code> : This tells the PHP interpreter youre defining a function<br>\n<code class=\"language-text\">dumper()</code> : ‘dumper’ is the name of the function when you call it<br>\n<code class=\"language-text\">($one, $two, $three)</code> : These are whats called “arguments” or\n“parameters”. These are what are passed into the function, this can be blank.<br></p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"99261631655510650000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`{\n  var_dump(\\$one, \\$two, \\$three);\n}`, `99261631655510650000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">var_dump</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$one</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$two</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$three</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p>This calls the function:\n<a href=\"https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.var-dump.php\">var_dump()</a><br>\nThis will output your variables onto the page.<br></p>\n<p>Lets get a little bit more advanced. Lets create a dd() function.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"59763877862268890000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.php\n<?php\n\n// Die and dump\nfunction dd(\\$val){\n  echo '<pre>';\n  die(var_dump(\\$val));\n  echo '</pre>';\n}\n\n// Will stop anything after this function\ndd('hello world');\n\n// Will not run\ndd('hi there');`, `59763877862268890000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Die and dump</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">dd</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$val</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'&lt;pre>'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">die</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">var_dump</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$val</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'&lt;/pre>'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Will stop anything after this function</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">dd</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'hello world'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Will not run</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">dd</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'hi there'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Lets look at what <code class=\"language-text\">dd($val)</code> is doing.<br></p>\n<p>So first, it defines the function dd, then it will take in a 1 variable argument.<br>\nNext, it will wrap the value of <code class=\"language-text\">die(var_dump($val)</code> inside of &#x3C;pre>&#x3C;/pre> tags.\nFinally, it will kill the execution of the php program. Equivalent to <code class=\"language-text\">exit</code>.</p>\n<h4>Homework</h4>\n<p>Assume you own a night club. Only allow people 21 or older inside and print a message\ntelling them if they’re allowed to come in.<br></p>\n<p>My solution:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"6970341241464984000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// functions.php\n<?php\n\nfunction isOldEnough(\\$age){\n  return (\\$age >= 21 ? true : false);\n}\n\nfunction echoOldEnough(\\$age){\n  echo '<p>';\n  echo 'You are, ' . \\$age . &quot;. &quot;;\n  echo (isOldEnough(\\$age) ? &quot;You can enter the club.&quot; : &quot;You cannot enter.&quot;);\n  echo '</p>';\n}`, `6970341241464984000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// functions.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">isOldEnough</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$age</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$age</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>=</span> <span class=\"token number\">21</span> <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> <span class=\"token boolean constant\">true</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean constant\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">echoOldEnough</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$age</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'&lt;p>'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'You are, '</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$age</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span> <span class=\"token double-quoted-string string\">\". \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">isOldEnough</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$age</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> <span class=\"token double-quoted-string string\">\"You can enter the club.\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token double-quoted-string string\">\"You cannot enter.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'&lt;/p>'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container customButtonContainerClass\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"7281811877837274000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied to clipboard!\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"5000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// index.php\n<?php\n\nrequire 'functions.php';\n\nechoOldEnough(21); // is allowed inside\nechoOldEnough(20); // is not allowed inside`, `7281811877837274000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy to clipboard\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">// index.php\n<span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">require</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'functions.php'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">echoOldEnough</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">21</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// is allowed inside</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">echoOldEnough</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">20</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// is not allowed inside</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I’m not going to go too in depth, but basically <code class=\"language-text\">echoOldEnough()</code> is a wrapper around\n<code class=\"language-text\">isOldEnough()</code>. This allows you to print a readable message on the webpage.<br>\nThis function is imported into ‘index.php’ when you run: <br>\n<code class=\"language-text\">require &#39;functions.php&#39;;</code></p>\n<p>Lets go to Chapter 11 in the next part.</p>\n<h2>Links</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/ParamagicDev/php-for-beginners\">Follow along with my repo</a><br></strong>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com\">Laracasts main site</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://laracasts.com/series/php-for-beginners\">PHP for beginners</a><br></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Learning PHP - Part 5 - Lets make it functional","date":"August 26, 2019","description":"Lets learn a little bit about functions"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/learning-php/part5/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/learning-php/part4/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Learning PHP - Part 4 - Lets get conditional"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/learning-php/part6/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Learning PHP - Part 6 - MySQL? Or Your SQL?"}}}}}